description.p:
The present invention further provides a method of operating a power distribution system comprising an ac busbar adapted to carry a variable-frequency ac distribution voltage, and an ac generator connected to the ac busbar and having an associated prime mover (e.g. a diesel engine, turbine etc.);

the method comprising the step of:

varying the rotational speed of the prime mover with reference to the electrical load on the ac busbar such that the ac generator provides a variable frequency output during normal operation of the power distribution system.

claim.claim-text:
A method of operating a power distribution system (100) comprising an ac busbar (2) adapted to carry a variable-frequency ac distribution voltage, and an ac generator (G1) connected to the ac busbar and having an associated prime mover (D1);

the method comprising the step of:
varying the rotational speed of the prime mover (D1) with reference to the electrical load on the ac busbar (2) such that the ac generator (G1) provides a variable frequency output during normal operation of the power distribution system.
